SIMPLE: foretell
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foretell
<hw>Fore*tell"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Foretold</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Foretelling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To predict; to tell
before occurence; to prophesy; to foreshow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Deeds then undone my faithful tongue <qex>foretold</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Prodigies, <qex>foretelling</qex> the future eminence and luster
of his character.</q> <rj><qau>C. Middleton.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To predict; prophesy; prognosticate;
augur.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foretell</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Foretell
<hw>Fore*tell"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To utter predictions.</def>
<rj><au>Acts iii. 24.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foreteller</ent>⟦br⟧
